com.interpss.core.aclf.hvdc

Interface VSCConverter<TBus extends BaseAclfBus<?,?>>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BaseConverter<TBus>, BusRef<TBus>, com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, NameTag, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    VSCConverterDyn
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    VSCConverterDynImpl, VSCConverterImpl

    public interface VSCConverter<TBus extends BaseAclfBus<?,?>>
extends BaseConverter<TBus>
    A representation of the model object 'Base VSC Converter'. HVDC VSC Converer

    The following features are supported:

    • Vdc
    • Pdc
    • Dc Set Point
    • Ac Set Point
    • Mva Rating
    • Ac Current Rating
    • QMvar Limit
    • Ac Control Mode
    • Dc Control Mode
    • Remote Control Bus Id
    • Remote Control Percent
    See Also:
    HvdcLinePackage.getVSCConverter()

      • getDcSetPoint

        double getDcSetPoint()
        Returns the value of the 'Dc Set Point' attribute. The default value is "0". Converter dc or power setpoint. For TYPE = 1, DCSET is the scheduled dc voltage on the dc side of the converter bus; entered in kV. For TYPE = 2, DCSET is the power demand, where a positive value specifies that the converter is feeding active power into the ac network at bus IBUS, and a negative value specifies that the converter is withdrawing active power from the ac network at bus IBUS; entered in MW. No default allowed.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Dc Set Point' attribute.
        See Also:
        setDcSetPoint(double), HvdcLinePackage.getVSCConverter_DcSetPoint()
